\item Convert the complex number $\frac{-16}{\myvec{1\\\sqrt{3}}}$

	\solution The multiplicative inverse of $\frac{-16}{\myvec{1\\\sqrt{3}}}$ is given by the following python code
	\begin{lstlisting}
	./codes/lines/q8.py
	\end{lstlisting}
	which is found as ${\myvec{0.25\\-0.43}}$ 
	Representing using matrices we get,\\
	\begin{align}
		\frac{-16}{\myvec{1\\\sqrt{3}}} &= \frac{-16}{\myvec{1&-\sqrt{3}\\\sqrt{3}&1}}
	\end{align}
Multiplying and dividing by the multiplicative inverse,\\
	\begin{align}
		\frac{-16}{\myvec{1\\\sqrt{3}}} &= \frac{-16\myvec{0.25&0.43\\ -0.43&0.25}}{\myvec{1&-\sqrt{3}\\ \sqrt{3}&1}\myvec{0.25&0.43\\-0.43&0.25}}
	\end{align}
	\begin{align}
		\frac{-16}{\myvec{1\\\sqrt{3}}} &= \frac{-16\myvec{0.25&0.43\\-0.43&0.25}}{\myvec{1&0\\ 0&1}}\\
		\frac{-16}{\myvec{1\\\sqrt{3}}} &= \myvec{-4&-6.88\\6.88&-4}\\
		\frac{-16}{\myvec{1\\\sqrt{3}}} &= \myvec{-4\\4\sqrt{3}}
	\end{align}
\end{enumerate}
